{"id":"queen-of-heaven","term":"Queen of heaven","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 7:18\">Jer. 7:18</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 44:17\">44:17</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 44:25\">25</a>), the moon, worshipped by the Assyrians as the receptive power in nature.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Jeremiah 7:18","Jeremiah 44:17","Jeremiah 44:25"]}